https://www.youtube.com/@DailyTimelapses.title: Daily Timelapses
https://www.youtube.com/@DailyTimelapses.description:
Please support our channel by subscribing! 

This way you can enjoy beautiful relaxing soothing daily time lapses with hand-picked music
So come in and start watching the beautiful view of the San Diego ocean!

Follow me on Youtube: https://www.facebook.com/pg/dailytimelapses/
 
You can see from the border up to downtown, and the camera allows you to see the weather changing at an elegant pace while enjoying some relaxing music.
This could be used as a background, with chosen video playlists displaying different kinds of timelapses depending on your tastes, you like them fast, you like them slow, we got them all :)

---- How do I do this every day?
The software I wrote generates, and uploads every night the previous day's timelapse captured by my camera.

If you have any request, like a different lapse speed or just a short piece slower or faster, please leave it in the comments with a date-range/time range and length of video :D and we'll get to it!

https://www.youtube.com/@SynekismInspire.title: Synekism Inspire
https://www.youtube.com/@SynekismInspire.description:
Synekism Inspire is a set of timelapse projects, the main one being a multi-year 1-picture-per-minute timelapse of downtown Toronto.

The main uploads will be daily automatic timelapse videos of Toronto from the previous 24 hours. There will also be occasional special timelapse videos of other places in the world or other parts of Toronto.

This channel is, in part, inspiration for the future of a city simulation game called Synekism. An archived early prototype of the game can be found here: http://www.synekism.com

https://www.youtube.com/@perpetualtimela.title: Perpetual Timelapse
https://www.youtube.com/@perpetualtimela.description:
NOTE: Unfortunately, the system is not currently in operation, with no plans to resume it in the future. The gaps present between some days are due to me constantly updating the system.

I love taking timelapses of the clouds and sky, and one day I had the idea to create a system that takes high quality timelapses every day and automatically uploads them to YouTube. The system controls a GoPro over WiFi to start, stop, and download the timelapse. Then, it adds music, collects and formats the metadata, and uploads it to Youtube. I'm quite proud of the result, especially given it was my first time coding in Python. Let me know what you think, and if you have any questions or feedback! Thanks for reading and have a great day!
